Problem 1

(a)

Write a Gibbs sampler using the conditional distributions provided in Example 7.4. Run your R code for p=5 and \(\rho = 0.25\). Verify that the marginals are all \(N(,01)\) NOTE: Okay the 500 iterations just says system.time = 0 so I’m bumping it up to 50000 so I can compare.

# Set up the parameters as in the question
  Nsim <- 50000
  p <- 5
  r <- 0.25

# Get the starting distributions 
  
  ## X0 should have p samples from the normal distribution
    X0 <- rnorm(p)
  ## The first x should have the save values as X0  
    XI <- X0
    
# Run the sampling 
  system.time( for (t in 2:Nsim){
     for (i in 1:p) {
      # Get X bar from the pervious iteration 
        avgx <- sum(XI[i-1])/(p-1)
      # Gather the current X with the formuala from 7.4
        XI[i] <- rnorm(1,(p-1)*r*avgx/(1+(p-2)*r),sqrt((1+(p-2)*r-(p-1)*r^2)/(1+(p-2)*r)))
     }
     X0 <- rbind(X0,XI)
   })
##    user  system elapsed 
##   53.62    2.52   56.15
# Plots
  par(mfrow=c(1,3))
  for (i in 1:p){
    hist(X0[,i],freq=FALSE)
    curve(dnorm(x),add=TRUE)
  }
